results.lead_paragraph: MOSCOW, June 3--Neil A. Armstrong, the first man to walk on the moon, obviously pleased an audience of several hundred Soviet scientists today by advocating closer United States-Soviet cooperation in space exploration and implying that the space programs of the two nations would eventually converge.
